Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Drain the @sweetcorn{160%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, fry the @British pork mince{240%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

== Couscous ==

Put the @couscous{120%g} into a #bowl{}.

Pour in the @boiling water{200%ml} (see pantry) and stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%g}.

Cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side, ~{10%minutes}.

Drain the fat from the mince. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

== Chipotle Pork ==

Add the garlic to the pork and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Stir in the sweetcorn, passata, @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @honey{1%tbsp}, @butter{20%g} (see pantry for both) and the remaining chicken stock paste.

Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little thick.

== To Serve ==

Fluff the couscous up with a #fork{}. Share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon over the chipotle pork.

Add a dollop of @soured cream{75%g}.

Enjoy!